âœ… PART 1 â€” Understand the Concepts (Simple Explanation)
ğŸ”¹ 1. What is a Jenkinsfile?
A Jenkinsfile is a script that defines the CI/CD steps.
Example steps:
checkout code
build Docker image
push to DockerHub
update Kubernetes yaml
push yaml to GitHub
Jenkins reads this file and runs it automatically.
A Shared Library is a folder called:
vars/
Inside it, you create .groovy files with functions that you can reuse in Jenkinsfile.
Example functions:
buildDockerImage()
pushDockerImage()
deleteLocalImage()
This keeps your Jenkinsfile clean.
Jenkins â†’ New Item â†’ Pipeline â†’ Pipeline from SCM
âœ… PART 4 â€” Configure Jenkins to use the Shared Library
In Jenkins:
Go to Manage Jenkins
Go to System
Scroll to Global Pipeline Libraries
Add new library:
Name: cloudLib
Default version: main
Load implicitly: checked
Source: Git
URL: your GitHub repo
