What ArgoCD does (high level)
GitOps controller â€” it watches a Git repository (or a path) and ensures the Kubernetes resources in your cluster match the manifests in Git.
Automated deployment â€” when Jenkins updates manifests in Git (new image tag etc.), ArgoCD detects the change and applies it to the cluster.
Self-healing & drift detection â€” if someone manually changes resources, ArgoCD can automatically revert to the Git state (self-heal) or alert.
Visualization & control â€” UI + CLI to view apps, sync status, history, rollbacks.
RBAC & multi-app organization â€” manage who can do what and group apps (app-of-apps pattern).
Role in your pipeline (how it fits)
Jenkins builds image â†’ pushes to DockerHub.
Jenkins updates kubernetes/deployment.yaml image tag and commits to Git.
ArgoCD watches that Git path â†’ sees the change â†’ applies the updated deployment.yaml to the cluster.
App is updated in cluster automatically (zero manual kubectl).
So ArgoCD is the deploymen
